---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../config/site";

const lastUpdated = "2026-05-07";
const contactEmail = siteConfig.email?.contact || `editor@${siteConfig.domain}`;
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description={`Privacy policy for ${siteConfig.title}.`}>
  <article class="legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <p>
      This privacy policy describes how <strong>{siteConfig.title}</strong> ({siteConfig.url}) collects,
      uses, and protects information about visitors and subscribers. Operated as part of the AI Sec Network.
      For questions, contact <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Information we collect</h2>

    <h3>Automatically collected (analytics)</h3>
    <p>
      We use privacy-respecting analytics (Plausible) which does not set cookies and does not track
      individuals across sites. We collect aggregate traffic data: pages viewed, referrer source,
      browser type, country (not city), and screen size. We do not collect or store IP addresses.
    </p>

    <h3>Voluntarily provided (newsletter)</h3>
    <p>
      If you subscribe to our newsletter, we collect: email address, the cluster preferences you
      selected, the source page you signed up from, and the timestamp. This data is stored in our
      database (Cloudflare D1) and synchronized to our email provider (MailerLite) for delivery.
    </p>

    <h3>Voluntarily provided (newsletter via direct embed)</h3>
    <p>
      Some sites in our network may embed newsletter signup forms directly. These submit to the same
      backend as the central subscribe page and are subject to the same data handling.
    </p>

    <h3>Cookies</h3>
    <p>
      We do not use tracking cookies. We may set a small functional cookie if you opt to dismiss a
      newsletter banner — this expires after 30 days and contains no identifying information.
    </p>

    <h2>How we use information</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>To deliver the newsletter you subscribed to</li>
      <li>To improve our content based on aggregate traffic patterns</li>
      <li>To detect and prevent abuse (rate-limiting, spam detection)</li>
      <li>To respond to inquiries you send us</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      <strong>We do not</strong> sell, share, or rent your personal data to third parties for
      marketing purposes. We do not use your data to train AI models. We do not run behavioral
      advertising.
    </p>

    <h2>Service providers</h2>

    <p>We use the following processors to deliver this site and our newsletter:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> (CDN, hosting, edge functions) — <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/">privacy policy</a></li>
      <li><strong>MailerLite</strong> (newsletter delivery) — <a href="https://www.mailerlite.com/legal/privacy-policy">privacy policy</a></li>
      <li><strong>Plausible</strong> (privacy-respecting analytics) — <a href="https://plausible.io/privacy">privacy policy</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>

    <p>
      Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to: access the data we hold about you,
      correct it, delete it, restrict its processing, port it to another service, or object to its
      processing.
    </p>

    <p>
      To exercise any of these rights, email <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
      We respond within 30 days of a verifiable request.
    </p>

    <h2>EU/UK GDPR specifics</h2>

    <p>
      For visitors in the EU/EEA and UK: we process your email address on the basis of your consent
      (newsletter subscription) and our legitimate interest (responding to direct correspondence).
      You may withdraw consent at any time by unsubscribing or contacting us.
    </p>

    <p>
      You also have the right to lodge a complaint with your supervisory authority. The list is
      maintained at <a href="https://edpb.europa.eu/about-edpb/about-edpb/members_en">edpb.europa.eu</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>California CCPA / CPRA specifics</h2>

    <p>
      For California residents: we do not sell or share personal information as defined under the
      CCPA. You have the right to know, delete, correct, and opt-out of any sale (which we do not
      conduct). Contact <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a> to exercise these rights.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>

    <p>
      This site is not directed at children under 13 (under 16 in some jurisdictions). We do not
      knowingly collect data from minors. If you believe we have, contact us and we will delete it.
    </p>

    <h2>Data retention</h2>

    <p>
      Newsletter subscriber data is retained for as long as you remain subscribed plus 30 days
      after unsubscribe (for unsubscribe verification and abuse prevention). Aggregate analytics
      data is retained for 24 months. Inquiry correspondence is retained for 12 months.
    </p>

    <h2>Security</h2>

    <p>
      We use HTTPS for all traffic, encrypted storage for subscriber data, and access controls
      limiting which network operators can read data. We have procedures for breach detection and,
      if a breach occurs that affects you, will notify you per applicable law (within 72 hours
      for jurisdictions requiring it).
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>

    <p>
      We may update this policy. Material changes will be flagged at the top of this page for at
      least 30 days, and we'll notify newsletter subscribers via the next dispatch.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>

    <p>
      <strong>Email</strong>: <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a><br />
      <strong>Operator</strong>: AI Sec Network
    </p>

    <p>
      <em>This policy is provided as-is for informational purposes and does not constitute legal
      advice. If you require legal advice, consult counsel.</em>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.legal { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 1.5rem 6rem; font-family: var(--font-body); line-height: 1.6; }
.legal h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 2.5rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
.legal h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.5rem; margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
.legal h3 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.125rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem; }
.legal .meta { color: rgb(var(--muted-fg) / 0.85); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
.legal p { margin: 0.75rem 0; }
.legal ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin: 0.75rem 0; }
.legal li { margin: 0.4rem 0; }
.legal a { color: rgb(var(--brand-accent-rgb)); text-decoration: underline; }
.legal a:hover { opacity: 0.8; }
</style>
